postcontent:
I had shut down an in-home IT consulting firm in December of last year.  I know its not really what you'd find on Armslist; however, if I cant sell it, I'd rather trade it to someone who can use it in return for firearms which have always proven to be a good investment.  I also have considerable experience with Cisco equipment configuration, as well as routing and switching, and edge security, ASA/PIX/VPN so if you have a small business I'd be willing to trade time or work at a flat rate setting up for you.

I am willing to take substantially less than cost, prices are listed for refrence.  This stuff has been sitting for over 6 months, so it really needs to go.

New in unopened box:  Cisco wireless access point, model AIR-AP1131G-A-K9.  Retails for almost $380

New in unopened box: Acer Aspire One netbook, model 722-369.  Slick little device.  Retails new $300+

new UPS batteries, 2 12V 17AH  APC model no RBC55

Several old 17" flatscreen monitors, used.  asking $30 each

box of keyboards and mice

Approximately 150 cell phones.  Most work and include batteries.  All take Cingular or AT&T SIM cards, would be a great chance to resell for parts or short term use... theres always an ad on craigslist of someone looking for AT&T phones cheap because someone dropped theirs in a toilet.  Most are flip-style, also includes a blackberry 9000, razors, treo's, and a bunch more.  Money making op here.  No chargers.

Ever since the business went under, I'm pretty well soured on technology, just would like this stuff gone and something usefull in its place.  Again, I know this isn't the usual Armslist stuff, so thanks for being patient.

I am a long-time Ohio resident, well over 21, current CCW, and receive yearly background checks for my current job.

It features an Apex Tactical Specialties forward set sear & aluminum trigger kit set at 3lbs, 360 degree grip stippling, and milled slide for a Trijicon MS03 red dot sight. Stock Barrel has been hand lapped to reduce leading when shooting lead reloads and is very accurate. The Trijicon Red dot is fully adjustable and also includes removable/stackable JP Enterprise’s elevation adjustment shims for custom loads. The slide Milling has been cut for this Trijicon sight but will also fit JP enterprises JPoint and Leopold Delta point sights. The Trijicon Sight also has a built in rear backup sight that still works with the front Novak Fiber Optic sight. This is a cutting edge pistol that has been quality built and needs nothing other than for you to sight it in for your custom reloads or favorite factory ammo. This pistol has very fast sight acquisition and is geared toward competition but can be used for a plinking or home protection as well (heavier trigger spring that is included is recommended for home protection).  It Includes 4 Factory 17rd magazines, case, stock takeoff parts and original paperwork as well.  The only wear this pistol has on it whatsoever is the Trijicon logo on left side of sight wears when the protective dust cover gets put on and taken off. title: For Sale:  Knights Armament EM SR-25 Match KAC 308
postcontent:
Knight's Armament has 21 years of experience in 7.62mm development, refinement, and service. The production of the earliest model SR-25's started in 1989. The SR-25 was first conceptualized with its primary function being a sniper rifle. It delivers remarkable shooting accuracy with .5 MOA being attainable in a multiple targer enviroment. The MK11 MOD0 and the M110 have embodied this experience and helped drive our company's renowned pursuit of perfection ultimately leading to the Enhanced Match Series of SR-25's.

The new Enhanced Match (E.M.) Rifle combines some of the best characteristics from the combat proven MK11 MOD0 and the M110 military rifles. The E.M. Rifle's Free-Floating barral is a clone of the legendary MK11 MOD0's, but its Upper Receiver Extending (URX) forend with integral folding front sight was developed for the Army's XM-110 Rifle. The E.M. Rifle's ambidextrous magazine release was also a noteworthy XM-110 feature and the lightweight butt-stock is the same as the MK11 MOD0's.

location: Mineral Springs, Waxhaw, Charlotte, North Carolina
postcontent: This is a nice Spanish made side-by-side 12ga shotgun that Davidson Firearms Company of Greensboro, NC imported.  26 inch barrels, improved and modified choke respectively, dual gold plated triggers (show wear from use), checkered wood grips, takes 2 3/4 shells.  As I understand these were imported during part of the 70's and early 80's.  Gun has some wear, and I expect someone used it as a field gun for birds, as it would be ideal for such.  No rust or damage, just some honest field wear from use here and there.  Fairly light gun with a great feel, locks up very tight and this one has the ejector and also the bolt-into-barrel lockup feature that only seems to be on about half of the model 63B's or fewer.  Quick take down shotgun... push button and remove fore grip, release barrels and remove, and you're broken down.  Didn't see another 26 inch barrel for sale like this right now.  Lots of nice hand engraving from Spain on this gun, very nice gun, always gets a LOT of attention when I have it out.  Only selling because I've got too many SxS 12's right now.   $400 cash
